I do unboxing and reviews of products that I buy for use by myself or at the ENGINEERABLE + SOUL BUILT shop. I spend a lot of time researching these products beforehand, so I already know that they are not shit when I review them.

description:
Who am I? 
I am Saulius Baradinskas.

What do I do in life?
I am a film, music video, and commercial director. I am also a screenwriter.

Why do I make this channel?
To share my journey as a filmmaker.

Some facts about my work:
✰ My directed videos reached almost 100 million views on youtube.
✰ I made three films and now I am working on the fourth.
✰ My debut short film "Golden Minutes"(2019) won traveled around the globe.
✰ This short film was shot in one take, on film, and the main role was created by famous Scottish actor Billy Boyd, who starred in Lord Of The Rings. 
✰ My second short film “Techno, Mama” had a premiere at Venice Film Festival.
✰ It was nominated as Best European Short film at European Film Academy Awards.
✰ I am BERLINALE TALENTS ALUMNI 2020

Some facts about my life:
✔ Proudly been a skateboarder for more than twenty years!
✔ I ran a full marathon!
✔ I graduated from architecture!
✔ I love meditation

More info about me www.baradinskas.com

The "Jack of all trades and master of some", Ian directs, produces, edits, creates visual effects, and gets his hands on the camera including certified jib user. Ian Morris was born and raised in the City of Sin, Las Vegas. He is a graduate of San Diego State's Television, Film and New Media program after serving seven years in the United States Navy.
His previous works are currently traveling the film festival circuit. "Fatal Fetish" was featured at the Latino Film Festival in March 2012 and also featured at CineVegas in June 2012. One of Ian's recent accomplishment is a Student Emmy nomination for directing the newscast production "Aztec News" at San Diego State University where he took on the tedious task of adopting brand new equipment in two days and creating a cutting-edge newcast.

description:
There is no underplay in the name Dope D.O.D. (Duo of Darkness). Their brand of music is sinister and sometimes difficult to stomach. They channel the dark undertones captured in American gangster rap and the macabre antics reminiscent of artists like Eminem.

Despite many of their obvious American influences they bring in elements from their homeland. They utilize the dark rifts that historically personified Dutch music culture, incorporating dark ambient sounds. But the group's most recognizable element is its electronic structure. 

Dope D.O.D. is unruly onstage and the audience is just as wild. Mosh pits break out on the floor as well as hardcore dancing. They jump around in a crazed havoc and incite the audience to go beyond the threshold of reasonable fun. 

2025, as Dope D.O.D. readies itself for a highly anticipated release and prepares to hit the road for an electrifying tour alongside Onyx, R.A. The Rugged Man & Benny Holiday, fans of hardcore hip-hop are in for a treat.

description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

description:
History

Located in Brooklyn, a brief 20 minutes from Manhattan, J&M Special Effects (DBA of Jauchem & Meeh, Inc) incorporated in 1985 and has since become the premiere go-to source for live special effects in the New York area.

Gregory Meeh, President and Head Designer, in association with Esquire Jauchem, founded J&M in a Soho basement with two fog machines and a passion for producing spectacular and innovative special effects for the performing arts community in New York. Jauchem moved to the west coast in the late 1980s to direct and produce for television; Greg Meeh became president of J&M and continues to foster the company's successful expansion. J&M recently moved into an 11,000 square foot warehouse space with 16 full time employees and the largest variety of effects equipment and products for rental or sale on the east coast.
